# C3 Notebook Application Context

When a C3 notebook (.c3nb) throws a ReferenceError like "TypeName is not defined",
the most likely cause is that the notebook is not connected to the correct application.

## Fix

The user needs to click **Select Application** in the notebook UI and choose the
correct package (e.g., `academyUI`). This sets the `appName` in the notebook
metadata so the runtime resolves types from that package.

## How to diagnose

Check the notebook metadata (at the end of the JSON): `"appName":"c3"` means it's
using the default runtime, which won't have custom types. It should match the
package name (e.g., `"appName":"academyUI"`).

## Do NOT assume

- Do not assume the package hasn't been provisioned.
- Do not tell the user to re-provision unless you have confirmed the app is
  already selected and provisioning truly hasn't happened.
